OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1774465894
OL,3,CDrink-driver disqualified for head-on
OL,4,Ccrash which gives victim 'flashbacks'
OL,6,FEmergency services who attended the
OL,7,Fscene said Lamont had glazed eyes, was
OL,8,Funsteady on his feet and there was an
OL,9,Foverwhelming smell of alcohol.
OL,11,FLamont was arrested and charged with
OL,12,Fcausing serious injury by careless
OL,13,Fdriving and drink-driving.
OL,15,FHe had 90 milligrams of alcohol per
OL,16,F100 millilitres of blood in his
OL,17,Fsystem. The legal limit is 80
OL,18,Fmilligrams of alcohol per 100
OL,19,Fmillilitres of blood.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
