PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1774465894
OL,3,CDrink-driver disqualified for head-on
OL,4,Ccrash which gives victim 'flashbacks'
OL,6,FLamont was also fined #455, and
OL,7,Fordered to pay #85 costs and a #114
OL,8,Fvictim surcharge.
OL,10,FInvestigating officer PC Jed Gobey, of
OL,11,Fthe Roads Policing Unit, said: "My
OL,12,Fcolleagues in the Roads Policing Unit
OL,13,Fand I are passionate about policing
OL,14,Fthose who choose to drive while
OL,15,Fimpaired or while under the influence
OL,16,Fof either drink or drugs.
OL,18,F"I can't stress enough, it is selfish,
OL,19,Fit is dangerous and it can change the
OL,20,Flives of you and others. Drink or
OL,21,Fdrive; never both."
OL,26,@sD@`OU}D@SO]
